    {
      "id": 22,
      "type": "bargauge",
      "title": "Chunks per NISD for VDev $vdev",
      "description": "How many 8-GiB chunks of the selected VDev reside on each NISD. Each bar is labelled with the NISD UUID and its hypervisor (hv) UUID. NISDs sharing the same hv label sit on the same host — if the VDev was created with a coarser failure domain (rack or PDU), the allocator only guarantees replica separation at that level, so multiple NISDs on the same host can legally accumulate chunks. Unequal bars across *different* hv values indicate a real imbalance; unequal bars within the *same* hv value are expected and explained by the failure-domain choice.",
      "gridPos": {
        "x": 0,
        "y": 79,
        "w": 12,
        "h": 10
